  <div>
    <h2>How it works</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <h2>Simple</h2>
        <h4>Quick and Easy</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Create a <%= link_to 'New Task', new_task_path %>.
          </li>
          <li>
            Enter a title and click "Switch Now" to start the timer.
          </li>
          <li>
            When finished with the current task, create a <%= link_to 'New Task', new_task_path %>.
          </li>
          <li>
            TimeFliesBy.com automatically ends the previous task for you.
          </li>
          <li>
            Any time you want to see your progress, click <%= link_to 'Tasks Summary', tasks_path %>.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h2>Flexible</h2>
        <h4>Unlimited Tags</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Create some <%= link_to 'Tags', new_tag_path %> up front, e.g.
            <ul>
              <li>Work</li>
              <li>Family</li>
              <li>Personal</li>
              <li>Household</li>
              <li>Play</li>
              <li>etc.</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
            Use them in your <%= link_to 'New Task', new_task_path %> or "Edit" in <%= link_to 'Tasks Summary', tasks_path %>.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <h4>You are in control</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>
            You can manually adjust the start and stop any time.
          </li>
          <li>
            We call this fudging.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h2>Streamlined</h2>
        <h4>Efficient Task Switching</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Starting a <%= link_to 'new task', new_task_path %> automatically ends the current task and starts the new one.
          </li>
          <li>
            Keep creating a <%= link_to 'new task', new_task_path %> to create a continuous timeline.
          </li>
          <li>
            You can effectively track your whole life, but who would want to besides me?
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h2>Tick-Tock</h2>
        <h4>Goes the Clock</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Time doesn't stop even though you may want to stop tracking it.
          </li>
          <li>
            Create a dummy filler task and let it run until you are ready to track again.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>

